    "description": "1993-151-31a - The two-sided, x-shaped white cardboard stand is imprinted on both sides. A rubber band, wound around the center, forms the x and holds the egg timer in place.\n\nRecto: The quotation begins on the left of the top strip and continues downward on the right, across the bottom, and halfway up on the left to the top:\n\n        The time which we have at our\/disposal every day is elastic; the\/\n        passions that we feel expand it,\/those that we inspire contract it;\/\n        and habit fills up what remains.\n\nThe second half on the left is imprinted Marcel (cheers from M&Co) Proust.\n\nVerso: On the top strip, 5 minutes is imprinted. Beginning on the left and continuing across the bottom and on the right is:\n\n         If anybody\/understands this quote,\/please write.\n\n1993-151-31b - A glass, hourglass-shaped egg timer is filled with white sand.\n\n1993-151-31d - The wrapper is a crumpled reprint of an article entitled Three Scientists Say Travel Time Isn't So Far Out (The New York Times, Tuesday, November 22, 1988).",
